.config/nvim/
├── after			-- last files loaded, "after" global and plugin settings
│   ├── ftplugin		-- specific file type settings, loaded after after/plugin 
│   └── plugin			-- plugin settings to avoid being overwritten
│       └── testprint.lua	-- testing init-lua structure using print statements
├── init.lua			-- start point of neovim lua config
├── lua				-- folder contains settings, plugin management and plugin settings
│   ├── packer.lua		-- file to manage plugin manager and install/manage plugins
│   ├── plugins			-- setup and settings for plugins (prefer lua plugins)
│   └── settings		-- global settings replace init.vim
│       ├── colors.lua		-- colorscheme settings
│       ├── keymaps.lua		-- keymaps that make this neovim my neovim
│       └── options.lua		-- setting for neovim options (and some notes on defaults)
├── old-init.vim		-- my old init.vim, good comments, not well maintained
└── tree			-- this file!

INFO
-- init.lua is the start point for neovim config, "requires" other files
-- The lua folder replaces old init.vim, split into sensible chunks - options, keymaps, color, plugins
-- The after folder ensures the things that should be loaded last are loaded last

NOTES
-- Avoids a superfluous "layer" in the file structure
-- Hopefully self explanatory (meaningful file names)
-- This config contains print functions to prove that this file structure works
-- If you run this as a neovim config you get print statements in correct order
-- Obviously remove the print commands and add your neovim config!
-- Uses "after" folder in a traditional vim way
-- Old init.vim ncuded, worked for me, but I didnt maintain it, I worked with it and around it
-- Plan to learn neovim better by developing this config and trying new stuff
-- Keeps neovim with lua config sane
-- Keeps me sane

